LC 255

A-Eng. HB 4007
1 SECTION 1. Sections 2, 3 and 4 of this 2026 Act are added to and made a part of the
2 Oregon Vehicle Code.
3 SECTION 2. Definition of “powered micromobility device.” (1) “Powered micromobility
4 device” means a vehicle that:
5 (a) Is designed to transport a person;
6 (b) Has a propulsion system;
7 (c) Has a maximum speed of 28 miles per hour; and
8 (d) Has an unloaded weight of less than 100 pounds.
9 (2) “Powered micromobility device” does not include:
10 (a) Devices exclusively powered by human power; or
11 (b) The following devices or vehicles:
12 (A) Electric assisted bicycles;
13 (B) Electric personal assistive mobility devices;
14 (C) Motor assisted scooters;
15 (D) Motorized wheelchairs;
16 (E) Motorcycles;
17 (F) Mopeds; or
18 (G) All-terrain vehicles.
19 SECTION 3. Application of vehicle laws to powered micromobility devices. (1) A powered
20 micromobility device is not a motor vehicle for purposes of the Oregon Vehicle Code, except
21 when specifically provided by statute.
22 (2) A person operating a powered micromobility device is subject to any provisions ap-
23 plicable to and has the same rights and duties as the driver of a bicycle, except when oth-
24 erwise specifically provided by statute.
25 (3) Subject to the provisions of subsections (1) and (2) of this section, for purposes of the
26 vehicle code:
27 (a) A powered micromobility device is a vehicle; and
28 (b) When the term “vehicle” is used the term shall be deemed to be applicable to powered
29 micromobility devices, except those provisions that by their very nature can have no appli-
30 cation to the devices.
31 (4) The provisions of the vehicle code relating to the operation of a powered micromo-
32 bility device do not relieve an operator or motorist from the duty to exercise due care.
33 SECTION 4. Local government and state agency regulation of the operation of powered
34 micromobility devices. Local governments, as defined in ORS 174.116, and state agencies
35 having jurisdiction over bicycle lanes, bicycle paths, sidewalks and trails of public passage
36 may:
37 (1) Prohibit the operation of powered micromobility devices on bicycle lanes, bicycle
38 paths, sidewalks and trails; or
39 (2) Regulate, by ordinance or rule and by traffic control device, the operation of powered
40 micromobility devices on bicycle lanes, bicycle paths, sidewalks and trails and the time, place
41 and manner of the operation of powered micromobility devices on bicycle lanes, bicycle paths,
42 sidewalks and trails.
