27 SECTION 22. ORS 153.633 is amended to read:
28 153.633. (1) In any criminal action in a circuit court in which a fine is imposed, the lesser of the
29 following amounts is payable to the state before any other distribution of the fine is made:
30 (a) $65; or
31 (b) The amount of the fine if the fine is less than $65.
32 (2) In any criminal action in a justice or municipal court in which a fine is imposed, the lesser
33 of the following amounts is payable to the state before any other distribution of the fine is made:
34 (a) $50; or
35 (b) The amount of the fine if the fine is less than $50.
36 (3) A justice or municipal court shall forward the amount prescribed under subsection (2) of this
37 section to the Department of Revenue for deposit in the Criminal Fine Account.
38 (4)(a) The provisions of this section do not apply to fines imposed under ORS 339.990.
39 (b) The provisions of subsection (2) of this section do not apply to fines imposed in justice and
40 municipal courts under ORS 811.590, [814.485,] 814.486, [814.534,] 814.536[, 814.600] or 830.990 (1).
41 SECTION 23. ORS 153.645 is amended to read:
42 153.645. (1) If a justice court enters a judgment of conviction for a traffic offense and the con-
43 viction resulted from a prosecution arising out of an arrest or complaint made by an officer of the
44 Oregon State Police or by any other enforcement officer employed by state government, as defined
45 in ORS 174.111:
[16]

A-Eng. HB 4007
1 (a) The amount prescribed by ORS 153.633 (2) is payable to the state and must be forwarded to
2 the Department of Revenue for deposit in the Criminal Fine Account;
3 (b) Subject to subsection (4) of this section, one-half of the amount remaining after any payment
4 required by paragraph (a) of this subsection is payable to the county in which the justice court is
5 located; and
6 (c) Subject to subsection (4) of this section, one-half of the amount remaining after any payment
7 required by paragraph (a) of this subsection is payable to the state.
8 (2) If a justice court enters a judgment of conviction for a traffic offense and the conviction
9 resulted from a prosecution arising out of an arrest or complaint made by a sheriff, deputy sheriff
10 or any other enforcement officer employed by the county:
11 (a) The amount prescribed by ORS 153.633 (2) is payable to the state and must be forwarded to
12 the Department of Revenue for deposit in the Criminal Fine Account; and
13 (b) Subject to subsection (4) of this section, the remaining amount of the fine is payable to the
14 county in which the court is located.
